<doc f='llvm/llvm/include/llvm/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.h' l='760'>/// Return the number of times the backedge executes before the given exit
  /// would be taken; if not exactly computable, return SCEVCouldNotCompute. 
  /// For a single exit loop, this value is equivelent to the result of
  /// getBackedgeTakenCount.  The loop is guaranteed to exit (via *some* exit)
  /// before the backedge is executed (ExitCount + 1) times.  Note that there
  /// is no guarantee about *which* exit is taken on the exiting iteration.</doc>
